{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00057", "completion": "\"If I declare ex:author rdfs:domain ex:Document , then a triple ex:alice ex:author ex:bob — where ex:alice is a Person, not a Document — will be flagged as a constraint violation; an RDFS validator will reject the graph.\" This treats RDFS as a type-checked schema language. It is not. Learners should be able to use this about rdf in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "common_pitfall", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_9db1be2db8b352b2", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-07", "co-18", "to-02", "to-04"], "prompt": "Use the idea of rdf to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 73, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00057", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00057]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s3"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
