{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00070", "completion": "The first of the two type-derivation rules is rdfs2 , which uses rdfs:domain assertions to derive types for the subjects of property triples. The rule is two lines long: If: ?p rdfs:domain ?C . A proficient learner can explain this about shacl in their own words.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_8f4b4729aba2ccab", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-08", "to-02"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind shacl for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 86, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00070", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00070]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
