{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051", "completion": "In Week 5, when you write SPARQL queries against a graph, you can choose whether to query the raw graph or the RDFS closure. Querying the closure means you do not have to write disjunctive patterns like \"researcher OR person OR scientist\" when subclass relationships exist; the entailment has already done that work. Learners should be able to use this about rdfs in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_263353dc6d979dca", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-07", "to-02"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of rdfs, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 67, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s3"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051", "completion": "In Week 5, when you write SPARQL queries against a graph, you can choose whether to query the raw graph or the RDFS closure. Querying the closure means you do not have to write disjunctive patterns like \"researcher OR person OR scientist\" when subclass relationships exist; the entailment has already done that work. Learners should be able to use this about rdfs in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_d472a7943a85645c", "instruction_variant": 1, "lo_refs": ["co-07", "to-02"], "prompt": "For an RDF/SHACL learner, describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of rdfs, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 100067, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s3"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051", "completion": "In Week 5, when you write SPARQL queries against a graph, you can choose whether to query the raw graph or the RDFS closure. Querying the closure means you do not have to write disjunctive patterns like \"researcher OR person OR scientist\" when subclass relationships exist; the entailment has already done that work. Learners should be able to use this about rdfs in a new but similar situation. [rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051]", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_19e7711e8d5e3e33", "instruction_variant": 2, "lo_refs": ["co-07", "to-02"], "prompt": "Give a source-grounded answer: Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of rdfs, and say why. Cite the source chunk in brackets.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": true, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 200067, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00051]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s3"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
{"bloom_level": "analyze", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00084", "completion": "The single most common conceptual mistake newcomers to RDFS make — and one that even experienced developers slip into when fatigued — is reasoning about RDF datasets as if they were SQL tables. The relational instinct says \"if the row is not there, the fact does not hold.\" That instinct is wrong for RDF, and the consequences extend through every later layer of the stack: queries return... A proficient learner can break this down and explain the parts of rdf.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_9fa30917c446b125", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-08", "co-18", "to-02", "to-04"], "prompt": "Break the idea of rdf into its component parts and explain how they relate.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 100, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00084", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00084]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}], "template_id": "analyze.explanation"}
