{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00010", "completion": "Every serialization syntax provides at least two affordances for managing IRIs: prefixes and a base IRI . Prefixes shorten frequently-used IRI authorities (e.g., foaf: stands for http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/ ); the base IRI tells the parser how to expand relative IRIs in the document. Learners should be able to use this about turtle in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_c325bbc676d7194e", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-03", "to-01"], "prompt": "Use the idea of turtle to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 26, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00010", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00010]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s21"}, {"confidence": 0.9, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s29"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
