{"bloom_level": "remember", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00003", "completion": "Describe the role of IRIs, literals, and blank nodes in RDF and distinguish the appropriate use of each node kind. An IRI — Internationalized Resource Identifier — is RDF's mechanism for naming a resource globally. Learners should be able to recall and restate this about iri without aid.", "content_type": "definition", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_8b4afdd5eaa630ff", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-02", "to-01"], "prompt": "State the definition of the central concept behind iri.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 19, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00003", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00003]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s1"}, {"confidence": 0.95, "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_primer_accessible#s7"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "role": "corroborating", "sourceId": "dart:rdf11_concepts_accessible#s2"}], "template_id": "remember._default"}
