{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00055", "completion": "The RDF Concepts and Abstract Syntax specification describes the concept of an RDF property as \"a relation between subject resources and object resources.\" RDFS gives you a vocabulary for talking about that relation: rdf:Property is the class of all RDF properties, and rdfs:domain and rdfs:range are the two predicates you use to declare the class memberships of a property's subjects and... A proficient learner can use this about rdfs in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_b6e169133613d096", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-07", "to-02"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of rdfs, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 71, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00055", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00055]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s3"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
