{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00074", "completion": "The fifth heavy-lifting rule, rdfs11 , makes rdfs:subClassOf formally transitive. The rule: If: ?A rdfs:subClassOf ?B . Learners should be able to explain this about rdfs closure in their own words.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_617d53d7a68b7324", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-08", "to-02"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind rdfs closure for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 90, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00074", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00074]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
