{"bloom_level": "analyze", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00075", "completion": "One subtle property of monotonic rule systems like RDFS entailment is confluence : the order in which you apply rules does not change the final closure. A reasoner can fire rdfs2 first or rdfs9 first; it can apply each rule until exhausted before moving to the next, or interleave them; it can run rules in parallel on different parts of the graph. A proficient learner can break this down and explain the parts of rdfs closure.", "content_type": "analysis", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_ebb35815d91c2036", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-08", "to-02"], "prompt": "Analyze the structure of rdfs closure and identify its most important relationships.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 91, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00075", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00075]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}], "template_id": "analyze._default"}
