{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00068", "completion": "An entailment regime is a precise specification of which triples a reasoner is allowed to derive from a given set of asserted triples. The phrase looks intimidating, but the idea is mundane: a regime is just a rulebook. A proficient learner can explain this about entailment regime in their own words.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_fa056b01e136521d", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-08", "to-02"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind entailment regime for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 84, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00068", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00068]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
