{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00095", "completion": "Week 4 took the informal \"the reasoner figures stuff out\" intuition you carried out of Week 3 and replaced it with a precise, predictable mental model of RDFS entailment. The procedure for choosing between them is mechanical: enumerate the axioms you intend to assert, and if any of them are OWL-2-only (disjointness, equivalence, restrictions, cardinality, property characteristics), declare as... A proficient learner can explain this about weeks 5 6 sparql in their own words.", "content_type": "synthesis", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_23affc1fc5fa887c", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-08", "co-23", "to-02", "to-06"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind weeks 5 6 sparql for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 111, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00095", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00095]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.65, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
