{"bloom_level": "remember", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00096", "completion": "Entailment regime A precise specification of which triples a reasoner is allowed to derive from a given set of asserted triples. RDFS, OWL 2 EL, OWL 2 QL, OWL 2 RL, and OWL 2 DL are all examples of entailment regimes; each layers more rules on top of the previous, producing larger closures from the same input. A proficient learner can recall and restate this about weeks 5 6 sparql without aid.", "content_type": "glossary", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_e9d4c00d1fa10d3e", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-08", "co-23", "to-02", "to-06"], "prompt": "State the definition of the central concept behind weeks 5 6 sparql.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 112, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00096", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00096]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.65, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s4"}], "template_id": "remember._default"}
