{"bloom_level": "analyze", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00110", "completion": "Common Pitfall: treating OPTIONAL like a filter When learners first reach for OPTIONAL , they typically reach for it because they want to exclude rows where a particular triple is missing — the way WHERE x IS NULL works in SQL. They write something like OPTIONAL { ?person foaf:mbox ?email . A proficient learner can break this down and explain the parts of inside.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_8d5e5033eacf23a8", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-12", "to-03"], "prompt": "Break the idea of inside into its component parts and explain how they relate.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 126, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00110", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00110]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#53c5b5712ac5afa8"}, {"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#6701991215d9bdb5"}], "template_id": "analyze.explanation"}
