{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00102", "completion": "A SPARQL query that referenced every IRI in full would be unreadable: a single triple pattern might run to 200 characters before you reach the variables. Language-tag comparison is case-insensitive ( \"@EN\" equals \"@en\" ) per BCP-47, but the lexical strings still need to match exactly. A proficient learner can use this about rdf term equality in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "page-title", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_7520991eab5c85e2", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-11", "co-09", "to-03", "to-02"], "prompt": "Use the idea of rdf term equality to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 118, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00102", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00102]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#b6bf39e648860d4f"}, {"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#f59f4f5b9b9a51c7"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
