{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00107", "completion": "This example extends the employees dataset from Content 6 with multilingual labels and a few imperfect data points so the filters have something interesting to work with. FILTER REGEX(STR(?label), \"corp\", \"i\") } Two notes: we wrap ?label with STR() because ?label may be a language-tagged literal, and REGEX requires a plain string in its first argument; STR() strips the language tag and... A proficient learner can use this about rdfs in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "page-title", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_b43b5a3921e9cf26", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-12", "co-09", "to-03", "to-02"], "prompt": "Use the idea of rdfs to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 123, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00107", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00107]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#b59dd96efbe6319e"}, {"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#25ba4fe7efa83f42"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
