{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00109", "completion": "In Weeks 1 through 4 of this course you learned how to model the world as RDF triples and how to declare reusable vocabularies with RDF Schema. This week introduces SPARQL 1.1 , the W3C-standard query language for RDF defined in the SPARQL 1.1 Query Language Recommendation. Learners should be able to use this about sparql 11 in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "page-title", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_f89eaa42157beace", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-11", "co-12", "to-03", "co-09", "to-02"], "prompt": "Use the idea of sparql 11 to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 125, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00109", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00109]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#f1221b72c605c26a"}, {"confidence": 0.75, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#2da0210f90dacd30"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
