{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00100", "completion": "SPARQL 1.1 queries follow a predictable skeleton fixed by the grammar ( SPARQL 1.1 Query Language § 19). Every SELECT query has three required parts — a prologue (possibly empty), a query form with its projection, and a WHERE clause containing a group graph pattern — plus an optional dataset clause and an optional set of solution modifiers. Learners should be able to use this about group graph pattern in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "page-title", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_3a17e4604407a2de", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-11", "to-03"], "prompt": "Use the idea of group graph pattern to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 116, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00100", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00100]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#997ebaa48b8c921b"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#2da0210f90dacd30"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
