{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00119", "completion": "By the end of this week you can author and run basic SPARQL SELECT queries against any RDF endpoint, restrict results with FILTER expressions whose three-valued logic you understand, model left-join semantics with OPTIONAL , express alternation with UNION and anti-joins with MINUS , and shape output with ORDER BY , LIMIT , and OFFSET . You can recognize the most common SPARQL pitfall —... A proficient learner can use this about sketch nouns and verbs in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "page-title", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_1a2361ff9bf2855b", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-11", "co-12", "to-03"], "prompt": "Use the idea of sketch nouns and verbs to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 135, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00119", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00119]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#f1221b72c605c26a"}, {"confidence": 0.75, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:sparql11_query_accessible#2da0210f90dacd30"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
