{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00254", "completion": "Week 11 · CO-25 · Reading the validated, enriched graph through SPARQL By the time SPARQL runs in the pipeline, the heavy lifting is done. The data graph has been ingested into RDF, validated by SHACL, and enriched by an OWL 2 reasoner. A proficient learner can use this about select in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_32bc39ab9cf06e99", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-25", "to-06"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of select, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 270, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00254", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00254]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s11"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
