{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00126", "completion": "A subquery in SPARQL is a complete SELECT query embedded inside the WHERE clause of another query. It runs first; its projected variables become bindings that the outer query can join, filter, and aggregate further. A proficient learner can explain this about mental model in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_d4b43f6aa66fee27", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["to-03"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what mental model means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 142, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00126", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00126]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
