{"bloom_level": "analyze", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00127", "completion": "Subqueries add a query level, and each query level is its own evaluation scope with its own planner pass. That has two downsides. A proficient learner can break this down and explain the parts of mental model.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_f76d980e1371d984", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["to-03"], "prompt": "Break the idea of mental model into its component parts and explain how they relate.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 143, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00127", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00127]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}], "template_id": "analyze.explanation"}
