{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00160", "completion": "SHACL Core's cardinality components ( sh:minCount , sh:maxCount ) are scoped by the sh:path of the property shape they live on. The cardinality counts the value-node set produced by that path on the focus node — nothing else. Learners should be able to explain this about node shape in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_ea4bef12e4a5f7fa", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-17", "co-18", "co-22", "to-04", "to-05"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what node shape means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 176, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00160", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00160]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#56204d5fd74aa93f"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#dc21cc2d99e62b9c"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
