{"bloom_level": "analyze", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00123", "completion": "DESCRIBE returns \"a single result RDF graph containing RDF data about resources\" — but the precise content of that graph is intentionally implementation-defined. The form has two argument shapes: DESCRIBE # describe a known IRI directly DESCRIBE ?p WHERE { ?p foaf:name \"Alice\" } # describe whatever IRIs the WHERE pattern binds Because output is... Learners should be able to break this down and explain the parts of quick recall.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_618bb738ee46e336", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-14", "co-09", "to-03", "to-02"], "prompt": "Break the idea of quick recall into its component parts and explain how they relate.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 139, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00123", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00123]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}], "template_id": "analyze.explanation"}
