{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00124", "completion": "Property paths are the SPARQL 1.1 mechanism for asking about connections between RDF nodes that may span more than a single triple. Without them, a query that needed to follow a chain — for example, \"every transitive supertype of :Cat \" — had to be written either as a UNION over fixed-length chains ( { :Cat rdfs:subClassOf ?x } UNION { :Cat rdfs:subClassOf/rdfs:subClassOf ?x } UNION ... A proficient learner can explain this about direct type plus all in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_362564338edaa55b", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-15", "co-09", "to-03", "to-02"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what direct type plus all means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 140, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00124", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00124]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
