{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00125", "completion": "A handful of patterns recur often enough that they are worth memorizing: Direct type plus all ancestor types. ?x rdf:type/rdfs:subClassOf* ?type binds ?type to every direct type of ?x and to every transitive supertype of those types. Learners should be able to use this about direct type plus all in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_93c140d41b319a94", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-15", "to-03"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of direct type plus all, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 141, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00125", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00125]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
