{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00120", "completion": "The basic graph patterns you learned in Week 5 return one solution per successful binding — every time the query engine finds a way to make the WHERE pattern true, it emits a row. That is perfect for retrieval ( show me every book Alice owns ), but it is the wrong shape for analytical questions ( how many books does each person own? A proficient learner can explain this about reading strategy in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_17731ccd4f277e23", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-13", "to-03"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what reading strategy means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 136, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00120", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00120]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
