{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00135", "completion": "Given the library data graph below, write a single SPARQL query that returns each author's name, total book count, and average page count, where the count is at least three. The aggregate-projection rule from the SPARQL spec restricts what the SELECT in a GROUP BY query may project: only grouping keys, aggregate expressions, and constants. Plan: the cleanest correct shape uses a subquery. A proficient learner can use this about sparql in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "page-title", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_6e4a61ba57f8a82f", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-13", "to-03"], "prompt": "Use the idea of sparql to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 151, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00135", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00135]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s6"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
