{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00165", "completion": "Financial-services firms run continuous data-quality validation on customer master records because regulators require it. Traditional approaches use stored procedures or a procedural ETL stage that catches \"missing tax-residency\" or \"malformed SSN\" by raising application-level exceptions. A proficient learner can explain this about auditor sanity check in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_f0fb146a0d3382a6", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-17", "co-18", "co-19", "to-04"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what auditor sanity check means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 181, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00165", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00165]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#56204d5fd74aa93f"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#dc21cc2d99e62b9c"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
