{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00152", "completion": "Every shape declares (or inherits) an sh:severity level, which is copied onto every result it produces as sh:resultSeverity . SHACL Core defines exactly three severity levels: sh:Info (informational; the result is recorded but the shape is intentionally permissive), sh:Warning (an issue worth attention but not blocking), and sh:Violation (the default; a real failure). A proficient learner can use this about authoring tip in a new but similar situation. [rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00152]", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_6fadd6ef4a42c103", "instruction_variant": 2, "lo_refs": ["co-16", "co-19", "to-04"], "prompt": "Give a source-grounded answer: Use the idea of authoring tip to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach. Cite the source chunk in brackets.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": true, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 200168, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00152", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00152]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#7855928147c8eafe"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#87f9dfcde0673761"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00166", "completion": "Most production SHACL deployments are not validating internal data — they are validating data flowing in from partners and external publishers. The validation problem there is harder than the internal case in two ways. A proficient learner can explain this about generalizes to every partner in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_9958ce81400eaa91", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-16", "co-17", "co-18", "co-19", "to-04"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what generalizes to every partner means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 182, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00166", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00166]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#61eb3930a076d977"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#56204d5fd74aa93f"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
