{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00158", "completion": "The SHACL specification draws a sharp line between two concepts that look similar at first glance: severity (the sh:Info / sh:Warning / sh:Violation ladder) and conformance (the sh:conforms boolean on the validation report). Severity is metadata attached to each individual sh:ValidationResult ; it tells downstream consumers how to react to a result. Learners should be able to explain this about operational consequence in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_9686a3bedafaa69a", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-16", "co-18", "co-19", "to-04"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what operational consequence means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 174, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00158", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00158]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#7855928147c8eafe"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#87f9dfcde0673761"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
