{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00143", "completion": "RDF was designed under the open-world assumption : the absence of a triple in your graph does not mean the fact is false — it simply means your graph does not know about it. This is exactly the right default for building a web of data where no one participant is authoritative. A proficient learner can explain this about reusability in their own words.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_6c56879c4a9b20b7", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-16", "co-18", "co-19", "co-22", "to-04", "to-05"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind reusability for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 159, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00143", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00143]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#799d33b7bb4efa68"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#d8e872e61b826838"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
