{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00176", "completion": "The sh:or parameter specifies the condition that each value node conforms to at least one of the provided shapes; it is inclusive disjunction (matches the everyday sense of or in English plus the technical sense of inclusive-or in Boolean logic). The constraint-component IRI is sh:OrConstraintComponent . A proficient learner can use this about composition before sparql in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_ba98debe2ca5ec9a", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-19", "to-04", "co-18", "co-22", "to-05"], "prompt": "Use the idea of composition before sparql to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 192, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00176", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00176]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.95, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#6fa327ca3fc0519c"}, {"confidence": 0.75, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#02ea99969917b186"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
