{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00179", "completion": "SHACL Core defines four target predicates: sh:targetClass selects all instances of a class; sh:targetNode names focus nodes individually; sh:targetSubjectsOf selects every subject of a given predicate; sh:targetObjectsOf selects every object of a given predicate. These four cover most cases. A proficient learner can explain this about custom targets keep constraints in their own words.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_e40341c3d7057811", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-21", "co-18", "co-22", "to-05", "to-04"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind custom targets keep constraints for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 195, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00179", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00179]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.95, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#313f76ddf0e027f1"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#8b8debe2ccc72b38"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
