{"bloom_level": "evaluate", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00180", "completion": "SHACL Core has another mechanism that can resemble custom targeting: sh:filterShape . A property shape's sh:filterShape restricts validation to those values that conform to the filter shape, effectively narrowing the set of nodes the constraint applies to. Learners should be able to judge the quality of claims about custom targets keep constraints against clear criteria.", "content_type": "analysis", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_6ccee66ee7d5638b", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-21", "to-05"], "prompt": "Assess the effectiveness of custom targets keep constraints against a clear criterion you state up front.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 196, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00180", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00180]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.95, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#313f76ddf0e027f1"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#8b8debe2ccc72b38"}], "template_id": "evaluate._default"}
