{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00183", "completion": "SHACL Functions are SHACL-AF's mechanism for declaring reusable, named procedures whose body is a SPARQL expression and whose interface is a parameterized signature. The motivating problem is duplication: in a large shapes graph you frequently find the same SPARQL fragment (\"compute the canonical capitalization of this string\", \"extract the year from a date literal\", \"look up the country code... Learners should be able to explain this about functions node expressions readable in their own words.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_6719485c1f6ac315", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-21", "co-18", "co-19", "co-22", "to-05", "to-04"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind functions node expressions readable for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 199, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00183", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00183]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.92, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#312d513458f95e8c"}, {"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#6d7011e3b1420dcf"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#13aa21cb2297e73f"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
