{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00184", "completion": "The combinator expressions are what give node expressions their compositional power. A path expression takes a node expression and a property path and returns the set of values reachable by walking the path from each input node — equivalent to a SPARQL property path traversal but expressed declaratively. A proficient learner can use this about functions node expressions readable in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_b3e1d2e2c38bf6c0", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-21", "co-18", "co-19", "co-22", "to-05", "to-04"], "prompt": "Use the idea of functions node expressions readable to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 200, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00184", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00184]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.92, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#312d513458f95e8c"}, {"confidence": 0.9, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#6d7011e3b1420dcf"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#13aa21cb2297e73f"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
