{"bloom_level": "analyze", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00191", "completion": "Common Pitfall: treating sh:not as \"value not in list\" When learners first reach for negation in SHACL, they reach for sh:not because the name is direct. That instinct is correct in many cases — sh:not is the right tool for \"value does not conform to a shape\". A proficient learner can break this down and explain the parts of heuristic.", "content_type": "misconception", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_d2516e85671b15aa", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-19", "co-18", "to-04"], "prompt": "Analyze the structure of heuristic and identify its most important relationships.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 207, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00191", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00191]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.92, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#6fa327ca3fc0519c"}], "template_id": "analyze._default"}
