{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00181", "completion": "Until this point in the week, every SHACL feature we have discussed answers the same fundamental question: \"given this data graph, does it conform to the shapes graph?\" SHACL rules invert that question. A rule does not check whether triples are present; it derives triples from existing ones. Learners should be able to explain this about rules change validation results in their own words.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_018d6f0876c9ce52", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-21", "co-22", "co-18", "to-05", "to-04"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind rules change validation results for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 197, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00181", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00181]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.92, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#0c6a8de9b389dadc"}, {"confidence": 0.7, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#617dabe19b2eff95"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
