{"bloom_level": "remember", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00199", "completion": "Week 9 turns from validation to ontology. Many of the validation requirements you reached for SHACL-SPARQL to handle in Week 8 turn out to be cleanly expressible as OWL 2 axioms; the SHACL/OWL trade-off — when to validate with SHACL vs reason with OWL — is the metacognitive thread that runs through Week 9 and ties Weeks 7-9 together as a coherent unit on RDF data quality. Learners should be able to recall and restate this about shacl core without aid.", "content_type": "transition", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_dbc07ae9e033da84", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["to-04", "co-22", "to-05"], "prompt": "State the definition of the central concept behind shacl core.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 215, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00199", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00199]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#617dabe19b2eff95"}, {"confidence": 0.85, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#02ea99969917b186"}, {"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_spec_accessible#6fa327ca3fc0519c"}, {"confidence": 0.75, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "contributing", "sourceId": "dart:shacl_advanced_features_accessible#0c6a8de9b389dadc"}], "template_id": "remember._default"}
