{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00209", "completion": "Cardinality restrictions constrain how many distinct values a property may have. OWL 2 provides three unqualified and three qualified variants: owl:minCardinality N / owl:maxCardinality N / owl:cardinality N — counting any value, regardless of class. Learners should be able to use this about quick comparison shacl vs in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "concept", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_a61312acc613881f", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-24", "co-25", "co-18", "to-06", "to-04"], "prompt": "Use the idea of quick comparison shacl vs to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 225, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00209", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00209]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
