{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00205", "completion": "RDFS lets you name classes; OWL 2 lets you define them. Once you have it, an OWL 2 reasoner can classify instance data: anyone who is a Woman and has at least one :hasChild assertion will be derived to be a Mother automatically, and anyone explicitly typed as Mother will be derived to be a Woman with at least one child. A proficient learner can explain this about defined class in their own words.", "content_type": "motivation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_dd986bbe5ff407d0", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "prompt": "Explain the core idea behind defined class for a learner new to the topic.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 221, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00205", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00205]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}], "template_id": "understand._default"}
