{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00207", "completion": "A frequent modeling decision is whether to relate a constructed class expression to a named class with owl:equivalentClass (defined class) or with rdfs:subClassOf (necessary condition only). Common examples in the family ontology: :Mother owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( :Woman :HasAtLeastOneChild ) ] — defined: Mother just is “woman with a child.” :Saint rdfs:subClassOf :Person —... Learners should be able to use this about defined class in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "synthesis", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_70943262b9b55cf1", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "prompt": "Use the idea of defined class to resolve a realistic problem; describe both the problem and your approach.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 223, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00207", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00207]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.3, "extractor": "content-generator-v1", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s9"}], "template_id": "apply._default"}
