{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00226", "completion": "Week 10 · CO-24 (apply) · Grounded in OWL 2 Primer Chapter 6.2 OWL 2 lets us declare that an object property is transitive , meaning that whenever two property assertions are linked end-to-end the corresponding endpoint pair is also asserted. That is what a property chain axiom expresses. Learners should be able to use this about property chain axiom in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_9fe9f7a22b8b67f4", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-24", "to-06"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of property chain axiom, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 242, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00226", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00226]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s10"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
