{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00252", "completion": "Week 11 · CO-25, CO-26 · Turning ontology axioms into materialized triples The first three stages of the pipeline give you a validated graph of asserted facts: every triple you ingested, no more, no less. This kind of class-defining axiom — a class definition built from property restrictions — is the heart of what CO-25 asks you to apply. A proficient learner can use this about cardinality restrictions in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_41dd72064f682b9a", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-25", "co-26", "to-06"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of cardinality restrictions, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 268, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00252", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00252]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s11"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
