{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00253", "completion": "The most useful pattern for the enrichment stage is the defined class : a class declared with owl:equivalentClass rather than rdfs:subClassOf . Hand-curated classification is expensive; defined-class classification scales with the size of the graph. A proficient learner can use this about cardinality restrictions in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_d246d31657df319b", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-25", "co-26", "to-06"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of cardinality restrictions, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 269, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00253", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00253]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s11"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
