{"bloom_level": "understand", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00246", "completion": "Week 11 · CO-25 · Naming the stages and the language each stage runs on A working linked-data system has the same shape almost everywhere you encounter it. Raw data — a CSV from a data provider, a JSON feed from an internal microservice, a relational table dumped through R2RML, a stream of events from Kafka — enters at one end. Learners should be able to explain this about ingest in their own words.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_fcd6ff4aaf92cd08", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-25", "co-19", "co-22", "to-06", "to-04", "to-05"], "prompt": "Explain in your own words what ingest means and why it matters.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 262, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00246", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00246]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s11"}], "template_id": "understand.explanation"}
