{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00255", "completion": "SPARQL 1.1 also supports SERVICE -clause federation, which lets a single query reach across endpoints. In a pipeline-driven architecture this matters because the pipeline produces a \"local\" enriched graph, but many applications need to join the local graph with an external linked-data source (Wikidata, DBpedia, a partner organization's public endpoint). A proficient learner can use this about select in a new but similar situation. [rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00255]", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_81232d89316868a4", "instruction_variant": 2, "lo_refs": ["co-25", "to-06"], "prompt": "Give a source-grounded answer: Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of select, and say why. Cite the source chunk in brackets.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": true, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 200271, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00255", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00255]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s11"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
