{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00249", "completion": "The third decision the ingest stage has to make is the datatype of every literal. Before declaring the ingest stage done: (1) every IRI is namespaced under a domain you control, (2) every predicate either reuses a published vocabulary or is documented in your own published vocabulary, (3) every literal has the right XSD datatype or a language tag, and (4) the mapping logic is deterministic —... A proficient learner can use this about ingest mini checklist in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_641b266160618c85", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-25", "co-18", "to-06", "to-04"], "prompt": "Describe a concrete situation where you would apply the concept of ingest mini checklist, and say why.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 265, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00249", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00249]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s11"}], "template_id": "apply.explanation"}
