{"bloom_level": "apply", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00287", "completion": "Week 12 · CO-29 · A repeatable five-step loop you run until the capstone conforms Use this procedure every time a SHACL run reports sh:conforms false on the capstone deliverable. The loop's purpose is to converge to sh:conforms true while ensuring that conformance reflects a correct vocabulary-data-shapes alignment, not a weakened shapes graph. A proficient learner can use this about read the validation report in a new but similar situation.", "content_type": "procedure", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_50970b138ffafd5d", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-29", "co-18", "co-19", "to-07", "to-04"], "prompt": "Walk through the procedure for read the validation report as if guiding a colleague doing it for the first time.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 303, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00287", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00287]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s12"}], "template_id": "apply.procedure"}
