{"bloom_level": "create", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274", "completion": "Why do we need all of them? RDF says what is ; RDFS and OWL say what it means ; SHACL says whether it is well-formed ; SPARQL says how to ask about it . Skip RDFS and OWL and your data has no shared vocabulary; skip SHACL and you have no defense against malformed ingest; skip SPARQL and you have no consumable query interface. Learners should be able to generate a fresh example or application of ingestion.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_2a40f0bfa0a51dc3", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-27", "co-19", "to-07", "to-04"], "prompt": "Propose a new explanation or analogy for ingestion that would help a novice learner.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 290, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s12"}], "template_id": "create.explanation"}
{"bloom_level": "create", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274", "completion": "Why do we need all of them? RDF says what is ; RDFS and OWL say what it means ; SHACL says whether it is well-formed ; SPARQL says how to ask about it . Skip RDFS and OWL and your data has no shared vocabulary; skip SHACL and you have no defense against malformed ingest; skip SPARQL and you have no consumable query interface. A proficient learner can generate a fresh example or application of ingestion.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_35ad0295bb4f0fed", "instruction_variant": 1, "lo_refs": ["co-27", "co-19", "to-07", "to-04"], "prompt": "For an RDF/SHACL learner, propose a new explanation or analogy for ingestion that would help a novice learner.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 100290, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s12"}], "template_id": "create.explanation"}
{"bloom_level": "create", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274", "completion": "Why do we need all of them? RDF says what is ; RDFS and OWL say what it means ; SHACL says whether it is well-formed ; SPARQL says how to ask about it . Skip RDFS and OWL and your data has no shared vocabulary; skip SHACL and you have no defense against malformed ingest; skip SPARQL and you have no consumable query interface. A proficient learner can generate a fresh example or application of ingestion. [rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274]", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_f2f4865b96f4fd0c", "instruction_variant": 2, "lo_refs": ["co-27", "co-19", "to-07", "to-04"], "prompt": "Give a source-grounded answer: Propose a new explanation or analogy for ingestion that would help a novice learner. Cite the source chunk in brackets.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": true, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 200290, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00274]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s12"}], "template_id": "create.explanation"}
{"bloom_level": "create", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00275", "completion": "Once the layers are clear, the pipeline almost designs itself. Stage 1 is ingestion : source data arrives in some non-RDF form (CSV, JSON, a relational database, an XML feed, a domain-specific format) and an emitter component transforms it into RDF triples in a known serialization. Learners should be able to generate a fresh example or application of ingestion.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_2e6a89e6ada5c015", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-27", "co-10", "co-19", "to-07", "to-02", "to-04"], "prompt": "Propose a new explanation or analogy for ingestion that would help a novice learner.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 291, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00275", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00275]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s12"}], "template_id": "create.explanation"}
