{"bloom_level": "evaluate", "chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00276", "completion": "Week 12 · CO-28 (defend) · The five questions every linked-data design memo answers The capstone deliverable is graded as much on the design memo as on the artifacts. The reason is that almost every linked-data project recapitulates the same five decisions, and every senior reviewer wants to see how a junior engineer reasons through them. Learners should be able to judge the quality of claims about memo anchor against clear criteria.", "content_type": "explanation", "decision_capture_id": "EVT_3f333439a4d6b033", "instruction_variant": 0, "lo_refs": ["co-28", "to-07"], "prompt": "Evaluate whether the core claim about memo anchor is well supported, and say what would strengthen it.", "provider": "mock", "requires_source_citation": false, "schema_version": "v1", "seed": 292, "source_chunk_id": "rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00276", "source_citation": "[rdf_shacl_551_chunk_00276]", "source_references": [{"confidence": 0.8, "extractor": "source-router", "role": "primary", "sourceId": "dart:owl2_primer_accessible#s12"}], "template_id": "evaluate.explanation"}
